live in the present moment i struggle so much when it comes to live in the present moment of the time i think about the past or worry about the future any tips on what could help me cause i want that to change get a piece of paper and pen and write down everything you are worried about think of all the different worries and memories that run through your mind do this as long as you can think of something else to worry about after a while stop thinking and start reading what you have written check off anything that you can fix change or cause to be different make a decision whether you are going to change or fix those things and then change or fix it or let it go the next time you want to go back to that thought or worry you can tell yourself that you have already taken that thought to its end you must understand that if you're awake you are thinking everyone is most people have very little idea what they thought minutes ago it's a noise that goes on you can escape it with entertainment it's hard to worry when you are engrossed in a good book or movie play games talk to people read listen to music dance these things are in the present and therefore so are you a good way to stay in the present is to get out of your normal routine do volunteer work take a class change jobs if you are working and you still find yourself to be only in the present then your job isn't interesting or demanding try juggling flaming swords that will keep you in the present good luck Milton H. Erickson Social rule Extreme Programming Debugging Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Kodocha Scenes from a Memory Piccolo Junior Saga Phoebe Halliwell Children of Dune Shaggy dog story Inflation Supply and demand Culture of Japan Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Philosophy of space and time The nature of God in Western theology Time Out of Mind About a Boy Dance Dance Revolution EXTREME Lucid dreaming Labour economics John Cage Fight Club Jiddu Krishnamurti Miss Saigon Alcoholics Anonymous Dr. Strangelove or: How